Posts.Content: BC Lifer reporting in . .I have been a member here for a long time . . I am known by most as the "bandlady"  I have been stage 4 since 1999 - originally diagnosed in 1997. I have taken pretty much every chemo there is and still take Xeloda & Tykerb orally every day. I will be in treatment for as long as the Lord lets me be here.  While so far I have somehow dodged organ involvement, I have no developed IBC on my arm??? and right breast -- you've got to admit it's always a challenge.  I live in Alabama and if you are in Tennessee, I see a meeting in our future.  Hang in there . .just do cancer on chemo days and Live, Live, Live!

Posts.Content: Hello ladies . . long time no hear from the bandlady of the board . . I am doing well . .still working, although I changed band jobs this fall, taking bi-weekly treatments of Gemzar/Herceptin (# 300 or 400+?) and living life to the fullest.  Kids are now 12, 14, and 21 and I can't believe I'm still here almost 10 years after it all began.  God is good.
Posts.Title: I speak for you!

Posts.Content: You are not gonna believe this  . . 9 years following diagnosis, too many recurrences to count, my infamous online BMT, hundreds of treatments, 5 times bald and my doc calls today.  Yesterday I had a PET/CT and it is CLEAR!!!  He told me there is NO EVIDENCE OF METASTIC DISEASE?!??!?!  He was stunned, kept looking over the report and reading it to me. I asked him what the plan is now and he doesn't have a clue . . .I am still on cloud 9 -- Of course the plan is to keep up my bi-weekly Gemzar/Herceptin, to keep me disease free for as long as the Lord allows, let my hair grow back and LIVE! LIVE! LIVE!

Posts.Content: Right there with you Cath on the "here we go again . ." After radiation in fall to shrink nodes under arm, I had a PET Monday only to find an "extremely suspicious area" in the right breast.  No real reason to biospsy I say . . I've had a rash there for months but onc didn't think it was anything. I wondered but thought it was due to swelling from lymphdema as upper left arm has the same rash.  Apparently it's more than a rash.  OK . .surgery not an option, more radiation would be extensive so he says Doxil.  I say "go fishing" . . I'm getting tired (whine moment there).  Do you lose hair on Doxil? I've lost it 3 times already and am not sure a 4th time is gonna work for me.
Posts.Title: Anyone on Doxil?

Posts.Content: Hey ladies . . . Well side effect #1 hit about 2 am Saturday.  It has been so long since I took Taxol I had forgotten all about the bone pain, but boy I remember now.  The problem I encountered was I was 2 1/2 hrs from home at an Honor Band.  I had no drugs.  I tried Tylenol, Advil, and Aleve with absolutely no effect.  I have a really high tolerance for pain, yet this was all I could think about all day long.  I finally got home last night about 9:00 and raided the cupboards looking for something to take -- I'm really not a junkie!!!  I finally found some Hydrocodone and had to take 3 over a four hour period before I could sleep.
Posts.Title: Abraxane side effect -- OMG, I forgot about the bone pain!

Posts.Content:
As I seem to be my oncs resident "clinical trial" I begin Abraxane this afternoon. . .Little bit of whining there, however, I do realize that I was also his Herceptin "clinical trial" and am still here 5 years later 
 .  Guess I'm cool as I can be about the 4th hair loss . . instead of looking for a wig to match my hair (which doesn't exist - and ought to be a clue to me it's time for a change) this time I picked out a wig and said, "cut my hair like this . . ."  Keith of course wanted to know why in the world I spent money to cut my hair when it would be falling out in 2 weeks . . lol . . I just told him I wouldn't be paying my hair dresser for a year and had to pay her one last time.  Of course all of you who know Keith, know that he is just messing with me and the best DH in the world.
